Initial Capture of patient demographics information\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\  primary actors: Doctor (Referring Physician)
                  Reference (Person who physically schedules the appointment. Nurse, secretary, PA, etc...)
                  User (Any one with credentials to access the system)
                  Radiologist
                  Patient

   Basic Flow of events:
      1. User logs in to the system with their supplied HIS/RIS ID and Password
      2. The System logs them in to thier respective portal
      3. Radiologist/Referring Physician selects add new patient or update returning patient
      4. The System loads the new Add Patient form
      5. Radiologist/Referring Physician fills out created form with new/returning patient's current demographics.
      6. The System sends the form information to the database for archiving
  
    Alternative Flow:
      1a. User credientials are not valid
        1a1. The System displays an error message
      2a. The System cannot connect to the database
        2a1. The System displays an error message
    
Referring Physician/Radiologist orders the desired radiology procedure\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
  primary actors: Doctor (Referring Physician)
                  Radiologist
                  Patient

   Basic Flow of events:
      1. Radiologist/Referring Physician accesses radiology portal
      2. The System loads the respective radiology portal
      3. Radiologist/Referring Physician selects modality Tab
      4. The System loads the modality Tab
      5. Radiologist/Referring Physician selects desired modality 
      6. The System automatically captures price and adds the charge(s) to the patient's bill
  
    Alternative Flow:
    
System prefetchs prior patient studies\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
  primary actors: Radiologist
                  System
   Basic Flow of events:
      1. Radiologist begins the process of taking the desired modality
      2. The system will automatically collect every prior study of the patient and display them within a seperate tab/table
      
    Alternative Flow:      

Radiologist completes modality worklist\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
  primary actors: Radiologist
                  System
                  
  Basic Flow of events:
    1. Radiologist follows the modality worklist steps and takes patient modalities
    2. The system will take the requested image of patient.
      
    Alternative Flow:     
 
Modality images aquisisition completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
  primary actors: Radiologist
                  System
                  
  Basic Flow of events:
    1. The system will save the image locally and send the image to the radiologist for approval
    2. The radiologist can either save the taken modality image for permanent archival.
    
  Alternative Flow:   
    2a. The radiologist approves of the taken modality image and saves it for archiving.
      2a1. The system will then save the image to the database
      2a2. The radiologist can either continue taking modality images or continue to next steps
    2b. The radiologist does not approve of the taken modality image
      2a1. The system will then loop back to the previous step "Radiologist completes modality worklist"
    
Modality image Archiving\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
  primary actors: System
                  
  Basic Flow of events:
    1. The system will automatically save all radiologist approved modality images and store them within an archival database under the        patient id and patient name
    
  Alternative Flow:   
    1a. If chosen, select images can be physically printed
    
Diagnositic Workstation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
  primary actors: Radiologist
                  System
                  
  Basic Flow of events:
    1. The radiologist can select any modality taken and view the image for diagnostics
    
  Alternative Flow:   
    1a. If chosen, select images can be physically printed   
    
 Report Repository\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\
  primary actors: Radiologist
                  System
                  
  Basic Flow of events:
    1. The radiologist can write a report
    2. The system will then store the report for Referring Physician access
    
  Alternative Flow:   
    1a. If chosen, select images can be physically printed     
    
 
